As the concentration of Hg2+ increased from 0 to 250 μg/L, the fluorescence intensity of ROR-CDs was significantly quenched (Fig. 3a, S3a). In the concentration interval of 0 to 20 μg/L, the linear relationship between fluorescence intensity and Hg2+ concentration was good (R2 = 0.9926) with a LOD as low as 191.69 ng/L (Fig. 3
                        b), while in the concentration interval of 20 to 250 μg/L, the R2 was 0.9910 with a LOD 1.82 μg/L (Fig. 3c). On the other hand, the fluorescence intensity of ROR-CDs showed enhanced effects as the CTC concentration increased from 0 to 50 μM (Fig. 3d, S3b). At 0 to 5 μM, the fluorescence intensity and CTC concentration were also linear (R2 = 0.9938) with a LOD of 12.70 nM (Fig. 3e). At 5 to 50 μM (R2 = 0.9939) with a LOD of 34.57 nM (Fig. 3f) (S/N = 3). The fluorescent probes constructed were compared with other current techniques for detecting Hg2+ and CTC (Tables 1 and 2

                        ). It showed that the probes ROR-CDs were comparable to or even lower than other methods in detection limits. In conclusion, we successfully developed a rapid, simple, and cost-effective fluorescent probe of ROR-CDs, showing excellent potential in detecting Hg2+ and CTC.

To verify the feasibility of detecting actual samples of ROR-CDs, Hg2+ content in tap water, river water, and lake water samples, the CTC content in chicken and milk samples was determined by ROR-CDs. The average spike recovery of Hg2+ was 94.78 % to 103.15 %, and the associated standard deviation was less than 4.17 % (Table 3
                        ). The average spike recovery rate of CTC was 99.86 %-105.64 %, and the relevant standard deviation did not exceed 4.83 % (Table 4
                        ). To verify the accuracy of ROR-CDs, the addition concentration of Hg2+ (GB 5009.268–2016) in water samples was detected by inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometry, and the addition concentration of CTC in chicken and milk samples was analyzed by liquid chromatography-tandem mass spectrometry. The results of the two conventional detection methods coincided with those of ROR-CDs, proving the reliability of the proposed methods of Hg2+ and CTC.
